metadata.name: Midsummer depression
metadata.description:
Let me tell you my secret.

I know Iâ€™m dying inside.
I drink my disappointment through my veins.
I hate my ugly hope, still have it daily.
I burn myself with my passion.

Anxiety spins my head round and round.
The envy seed burrow in my body.
Lay down and Pretending everything fine.

But in the end of the day,
I do no quit.
